cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is about named entity recognition (NER) in conversational texts using transfer learning with pretrained language models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses unsupervised learning and inductive biases, which are relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with information retrieval, which is relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper involves neural networks, which makes cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible sub-category.
